Replaces the rightmost occurrence of a pattern with another string, in-place.

# Examples

Basic usage:

```
#![feature(string_replace_in_place)]

let mut s = String::from("Test Results: ❌❌❌");

// Replace the rightmost ❌ with a ✅
s.replace_last('❌', "✅");
assert_eq!(s, "Test Results: ❌❌✅");
```
